    <p xml:id="auto_kbz4ip3t">
        <m>{\color{black} \textbf{Key Takeaway}}</m>
    </p>
    <p xml:id="auto_fe3b2pdc">
        Two events are mutually exclusive if they cannot occur at the same time.
    </p>
    <p xml:id="auto_5aabaa75">
        This means that if one event happens, the other cannot.
    </p>
    <p xml:id="auto_jh80mef8">
        If <m>\textbf{A} </m> and <m>\text{B}</m> are mutually exclusive events, then;
        <md>
            <mrow> \textbf{P(A and B) = 0} </mrow>
        </md>
    </p>
    <p xml:id="auto_gdwtztg1">
        <md>
            <mrow> \textbf{P}(\textbf{A} \cap \textbf{B} ) \, = \, 0 </mrow>
        </md>
    </p>
    <p xml:id="auto_jysiv2a0">
        The probability of either <m>\textbf{A}</m> or <m>\textbf{B}</m> occurring is;
        <md>
            <mrow>\textbf{P(A or B) = P(A) + P(B)} </mrow>
        </md>
    </p>
    <p xml:id="auto_gg5v9ly2">
        <m>\text{Example} </m>
        <ul xml:id="auto_o3i6ztt3">
            <li xml:id="auto_rd3wrv4q">
                <p xml:id="auto_s52u8lii">
                    A traffic light being red and the same traffic light being green at the exact same time.
                </p>
            </li>
            <li xml:id="auto_tt9chdid">
                <p xml:id="auto_be8t0n8l">
                    You are sleeping and you are wide awake at the exact same moment.
                </p>
            </li>
            <li xml:id="auto_uyhkgr4w">
                <p xml:id="auto_lxwrlsbp">
                    A door being open and the same door being closed at the same time.
                </p>
            </li>
        </ul>
    </p>

    <axiom component="lesson-plan">
        <title>Practice and Application</title>
        <p xml:id="auto_y5dgemui">
            <dl>
            <li xml:id="auto_sxs3oddp">
